Neural networks are at the heart of everyday technology - recognition systems.
Mathematical ideas are the core of how they work.

Some tasks are easy for computers, but hard for humans - multiplying millions of pairs of numbers.
Some tasks are hard for computers, but easy for humans - recognising faces in a photo of a crowd.


